The State Capture Inquiry will hear Passenger Rail Agency of South Africa (PRASA) related evidence on Tuesday. JOHANNESBURG - The State Capture Inquiry will hear Passenger Rail Agency of South Africa (PRASA) related evidence on Tuesday. Former Prasa CEO, Lucky Montana will continue his testimony. The Commission will also hear evidence from the Head of the Legal Division at Prasa, Martha Ngoye and Prasa employee, Mr Tiro Holele.